      "role": "user",
      "content": "That's good to hear, but I was looking closer at the variance in the weekly symptom counts for the second half of the trial. It looks like some of the responder subgroups are swinging pretty wildly from day to day. If I report a 95% reduction to the board with this level of noise in the raw data, they're going to grill me on why the confidence intervals aren't much tighter. Are you sure the current model isn't smoothing over some of that volatility to give us a cleaner projection?",
