      "content": "I understand your concern, and I agree that the raw data can be noisy. However, I've run multiple sensitivity analyses, and our model is actually quite robust to those fluctuations. The smoothing effect is intentional, as it allows us to capture the overall trend and reduce the impact of short-term variability. I've also considered the possibility of a \"placebo effect\" in the second half of the trial, where some participants may have been experiencing a natural recovery from their symptoms, which could be contributing to the variability. Our model accounts for this by weighting the data more heavily towards the first half of the trial, where the treatment effect is more pronounced.",
